To stop trying to love my body in an emotions driven way the butterflies in the stomach way we romance love. Love is action. Love is showing up. So instead of constantly asking myself (and failing at) "how do I love myself today?" I ask myself "how do I show up for myself today?"'.

node.text:
Let’s expand. 

Let’s say you meet the person of your dreams. Your heart is a racing with wonder. The butterflies in your stomach are fluttering. 

But this is not love. 
Is it? 

Because love doesn’t last with a racing heart and butterflies in the stomach. 

Love lasts when you show up. 
Love lasts when you stop expecting butterflies all the time, and translate the energy to action. 

Many times when we speak of self love we speak it as self attraction. Am I attracted to me? Am I attractive to others? 

Love as an action merely says: how can I show up for this love? How can I show up for myself IN love? how can I show up for others. 

This perspective is what changed it all for me.

Because self love shouldn’t be just another thing we feel we are failing at. 
It has to leave room for sadness and grief and frustration and joy. It is love in action to it all. 

Motions over emotions.

node.text:
Tired of feeling bad ~ about feeling bad ~ about my body some days when others days I feel completely at peace. Because the opposite used to be true and it was all bad days, no rest, no peace. 

Grief if a processing tool. 
One that allows me to move through the ebbs so I may flow. 
I don’t feel bad for it anymore. 
I cannot. 
For I am practicing the work of dismantling how I view my body and my worth and that’s not done in sunshine and lollipops but in feelings 
and moving 
and shaking 
and breathing 
and being. 

Feeling bad some days. 
So I can feel peace most days. 

Stretch marks of the soul.

node.text:
What do sharks and skincare have to do with each other? Sadly, a lot. 

Good news is @biossance is doing something about it. By harvesting Squalane from sustainable sugarcane instead of from the livers of sharks, over 2 million sharks are saved every year! 

After discovering @biossance in 2019, it’s been a part of my routine ever since. Especially since becoming pregnant and breastfeeding because it’s all safe to use. 

From the new Squalane + Amino Aloe Cleanser to my holy grail Squalane Probiotic Gel Moisturizer (I’m on my third jar!), Squalane + Peptide Eye Gel and the Squalane + Vit C Rose Oil, I’m a big fan! 

Plus, the sharks! 
Did you know my first tattoo ever was of a shark? True story. It’s on my foot🦈!

Find @biossance on their website or at @sephora @sephoracanada! #ad

node.text:
I barely recognize myself. 

Last time I felt this way, I crash dieted for 2 years and landed myself in some really dark waters. 

Now I barely recognize myself and I realize:
A) I’ve been through a lot this last year and my body has been carrying me/us through it. 
B) I’ve literally never taken a mirror to see myself sitting on a rock in the middle of a lake so I mean, new reflections! 

Change is uncomfortable. 
Leaning into it instead of pacifying it, is a whole new strategy. 

If only there were stretch marks on the soul to show my growth from within 🤍

node.text:
☁️G I V E A W A Y☁️

He’s waited years for this! Finally, Bo is getting his own fresh set up from mattress, pillow, protectors and bedding + a room makeover to suit his tween needs before school is back in session! 

At this age, sleep is a bigger battle than with a newborn, I swear! Sleep is so important to set our kids up for success and optimal sleep is something I know starts with a restful space. 

His last couple mattresses were over a decade old hand-me-downs, which worked as long as they could and Bo never complained! But when I told him a new mattress was on the way AND bedding - I could not have anticipated how overjoyed he would be. 

And well, we’re hoping we can throw that kind of joy back out into the world. 

With the help from my friends @sleepcountrycan we’re giving away to one lucky person/family a $5000 gift card to upgrade your sleep, spend on anything you may need from mattresses, sleep accessories & more.

💤To enter💤
🛌Follow @sleepcountrycan and myself @thebirdspapaya
🛌Comment with what YOU’d like to use that $5000 on! (A king size bed? Crib mattress? Bedding? Dog bed? ALL OF THE THINGS?) 
🛌Tag friends (each comment is an entry!) 

This give away is open exclusively to residents of Canada (excluding Quebec). Must be 18+ to enter. Give away will be closed at 8 PM EST on August 18, 2021. Winners will be announced on August 19, 2021 via comment and direct tag on this Instagram post. Thank you to our #partner @sleepcountrycan. This promotion is in no way sponsored, endorsed or administered by, or associated with, Instagram. 

@sleepcountrycan #sponsored #SleepWellStayWell

node.text:
Don’t let people who have never lived a day in your body tell you that the results of YOUR life / growth / change aren’t valid or normal. They are. Even if it’s different from someone else’s valid and normal experience for themselves and their life. 

Also who said we wanted to be normal? Sounds boring. ✌️

Behind every great outfit is a friend you texted the night before asking for advice on what to wear and how to style it🙏🙏🙏 

I say this because a lot of us just think folks just *have* style and forget a lot of the self doubt that comes with or the advice given along the way. We all are kinda just winging it, aren’t we? 

Anyways. Here’s my outfit!
